<p itemprop="description">Business analysis involves investigating business processes, identifying requirements, analysing problems, and recommending solutions to help organisations improve performance and achieve their objectives.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can understand the role of business analysis in projects and change initiatives. You recognise different types of requirements and basic analysis techniques.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can gather and document requirements, analyse business processes, and use basic business analysis techniques to investigate problems and propose solutions.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can lead complex business analysis activities, facilitate stakeholder workshops, perform detailed gap analysis, and recommend comprehensive solutions to business problems.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can establish business analysis methodologies and standards, lead enterprise-wide analysis initiatives, and mentor others in advanced business analysis techniques.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

